Ranger of Norath</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">The story of Tymoria Brightblade is a simple one really.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<br>
She started out a somewhat timid ranger lass from Surefall Glade, minding her guild master carefully, killing gnolls where she found them and hunting all but wolves and bears. <br>
She very much disliked Black Burrow and rarely endeavored to hunt inside the filthy dark place, but chose instead to hunt the Gnoll Watchers outside of the caves. Keeping the gnolls inside blind to the happenings of the world in this way was quite satisfying for her. <br>
<br>
<br>
Slowly acquiring money doing this she managed to buy her first set of Banded armor and was very proud of herself, but as a ranger of the 10th circle she still had only her practice blade. She dreamed of doing greater harm to her foes and of finding a mentor other than Hager Sureshot. For although he was wise, he was not much for simply sharing the events of the day and wasnt much for companionship. <br>
<br>
<br>
So it was one day that she came upon some grief in the Western plains of Karana and was running bare as the day she was born from the Qeynos Hills to Western Karana to retrieve her gear when a kind ranger woman stopped her to see if she needed aide. <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh,&quot; said she, <br>
&quot; I simply need to go get my gear from the guard tower and continue hunting friend, something I believe I can manage without TOO too much difficulty so long as I dont run into the rather aggressive cats of the plains on the way.&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
She then prepared to do just that when the kind ranger woman began to cast a spell upon her, Spirit of the Wolf! Her feet would FLY the distance! <br>
Then the kind ranger said, <br>
&quot; I will escort you to your gear, if it isnt too far then it is surely along my way anyway, I wouldnt want you to come to grief, and it is really no trouble,&quot; <br>
<br>
and so, the two ranger women, one young lass and one more seasoned woman headed off to collect Tymoria's gear. <br>
<br>
<br>
Ahh, but once her gear was back where it belonged, the ranger woman wanted to take a look at Tymoria's sword! Quite mortified that so great a ranger as this would see her poor excuse for a blade, Tymoria extended the blade for Merani to see. Upon seeing such a pitiful blade in the girl's hands, instead of scornfully ridiculing the blade, she handed her a much larger and difficult to handle blade, a two hander in fact! Upon examining it Tymoria realized that this was a Sarnak Ceremonial Sword! <br>
<br>
<br>
A great sword for so lowly a ranger she thought, and thanked her benefactor thoroughly and well. She also mentioned how dissatisfied she was without a family and mentor to turn to and how she wished she could find a guild to call home, to wich the Lady replied, <br>
&quot; You wish to be part of a guild?&quot; <br>
An eager nod, <br>
&quot; Well then! I am one member of a very new and exciting guild called the Arrow of Light! We believe in helping one another and all confused or stricken individuals of Norath! Would you be interested in calling our guild your home?&quot;<br>
<br>
Overwhelmed, Tymoria gushed her approval and agreed to wait for her new mentor to contact her with the guildleader for her formal invitation into the Arrow of Light. <br>
<br>
<br>
The story of her journey to meet this Guild Master is certainly a long and harrowing one, to be told later when you have the chance to prepare for it better. <br>
<br>
<br>
So now, with a Guild, and with a new and beloved mentor, Merani, Tymoria went forth into Norath with renewed vigor to smite the evil creeping across the land. There were many things she learned then, including fletching, but that, my friends, is yet another story for another day . . . . ..<br>
<br>
