The Journey Home<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>We resume our story to tell the tale <br>
of Tymoria's journey to meet <br>
Aydrian Silverain,<br>
Guild Leader of The Arrow Of Light</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
After many weeks of waiting and hoping she was seen as good enough to join such a wonderus sounding guild as The Arrow Of Light, Tymoria finnaly grew too large in her skills for the small world of her home in Qeynos. She tentatively asked a friend wizzard of twenty some odd seasons named Deloit to aid her in crossing the Karanas, for although she was adept at avoiding the dangers of West Karana, she knew that North Karana would surly be too much for her. Deloit said that she would have much luck meeting new people and fighting for good in a land called The Oasis of Marr, there was a terrible orc problem there that needed quelling and to this day despite the efforts of many, they still thrive in that highway of evil. <br>
<br>
<br>
Agreeing to try out this new prooving ground, Tymoria began the journey there with Deloit. First and foremost Deloit cast a spell of invisibility on her, she would be far too tempting a morsel for the evil plagueing thier route. <br>
<br>
<br>
The journey through the Karanas went fairly without event, they crossed many strange and unknown creatures to Tymoria, Griffawns and several varieties of gigatic and fearsom spiders that she simply did not want to contemplate doing battle with.<br>
<br>
<br>
along her way, she was contacted by Merani! (Merani had slowly gained a god-like respect from Tymoria by now, being such an experienced and worldly ranger) Tymoria and Merani were able to hold a short conversation along her way through the Karanas and decided to meet at the edge of the Forest of Kithicor, where Merani would take over escorting Tymoria and bring her not to the Oasis, but to Aydrian Silverain in the Lavastorm Mountains; several fearsom sounding locations to Tymoria's mind, but for now she had Deloit to protect her and later would have Merani, so no need to too worried yet.<br>
As Deloit and Tymoria approached the edge of Kithicor they saw Merani standing there waiting for them and while they waited for daytime to come, (wich was impossible for Tymoria, she could not understand HOW one could tell time in such a smog) they aquanted themselves with each other and there was a flurry of mutualy benificial spell casting between Merani and Deloit. Tymoria was able to add her Feet Like Cat spell to the mix, but with two such mighty companions felt it was much like a mere drop of water in a great lake! When Tymoria inquired as to why they had to wait for &quot;daybreak&quot; Merani and Deloit gave a shiver and replied that she did not want to know, simply do not ever travel there from dusk to dawn, for peril of your life. <br>
<br>
<br>
Well this was quite enough information to give our young ranger a fluttering tummy for the rest of that harrowing journey to the other side of this fearsom forest. She could not stop looking over her shoulder and was frantic not to lose Merani in the murk. <br>
<br>
<br>
Well eventualy they found rest as they broke into the Western Commonlands. This place still held dangers, but in the light of day for real at least. So, staying invisible, she and Merani traveled from the West Commonlands to the East, and there they met thier next challenge. . . . Nektulos Forest, playground of the Darkelves.<br>
<br>
<br>
In this dark and frightening land, Merani made double sure that not only Tymoria, but she too, were both invisible for the journey. For although Merani enjoys nothing more than to kill Dark elves, Tymoria was not yet old enough for the task and going into such a battle unpartnered may as well have been suicide plain and simple. I will not speak of the creatures they came oacross, they are too frightfull to make an accruate account of without inducing you to nightmares forevermore. But there were several occasions where the young ranger girl thought they had met thier end to be sure. <br>
<br>
<br>
Finaly they passed out of the forest and into a craggy pass leading into the Lavastorm Mountains. At last! There was a figure waiting for them in the pass in striking blue armor and, amazingly enough, a half elven countenance! Merani stepped up to him and exchanged words and an embrace. She then turned about slightly and said to him, &quot; Aydrian, this is Tymoria, a young ranger I met some time ago in West Karana, she niether looked for nor expected help or reward when we met, but gladly accepted both, and today has made the harrowing journey from Qeynos to meet you here tonight. She never doubted or hesitated on any leg of this long run, I believe her to be propor material for our young guild. What say you?&quot; <br>
<br>
<br>
There were much gestures and jests made by Aydrian that at the time, Tymoria simply could not take in, she was in awe of seeing this warrior, who to her spelled certain death if she were to cross him, and yet seemed so jovial and kind hearted. She had never met the like on Norath. <br>
<br>
<br>
So it was with much gentle teasing of thier shy young recruit that Aydrian Silverain formaly invited Tymoria into the fold of the Arrow of Light! At first there was simple too much going on all of a sudden to comprehend! There were so many voices in her head it seemed far too crowded to hold them all!<br>
