<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This story picks up after <br>
Tymoria's meeting with <br>
Aydrian Silverain and Merani.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> </div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> <br>
<br>
The couple escorted Tymoria out of Nektulos Forest back to the Commonlands and on to the city of Freeport. Upon reaching the bank in Freeport she was introduced to a great pillar of a barbarian named oddly enough. . . Bangoo! With a great chuckle and a charming highlands accent he greeted Tymoria warmly and with open arms; and Great Karana what large arms they were! After asking politely to take the liberty of inspecting her gear, he pronounced that she was not using a bow fit for a ranger, and handed her a new one. She had never dreamed of such a bow! Much less thought she would ever own one it's like! It was called a Shaped Darkwood Compound Bow; this bow had such a range to it that Tymoria could barely see the evil she shot at! <br>
<br>
<br>
Well from there the great man took her out to the dessert of Ro for some training such as she had always wanted! He explained tactics and strategy and such to her, things that always had been a mystery to her, he explained at last. It was the most fun she had ever had. He would venture out into the great desert and find some gruesome insect or another for her to kill, after deciding if it was enough of a challenge for her, he let her have at it with a vengence . . .ahhh a grand time was had in Ro that day! <br>
Throughout the battles, during periods of rest and recovery, she would listen to, and occasionally contribute to, the conversations of her new guild. It happened that Merani wondered weather Tymoria had begun her fletching yet. So wondering, she asked her. Tymoria replied that no she hadn't, the arrows sold at the merchants stall in Surefall Glade had always been sufficient when she could afford them. Well obviously Merani was shocked at the least! <br>
&quot; Any ranger worth her salt fletches Tymoria, it is by far THE most useful skill you can learn as a ranger! Why the bow you now carry may only be had by way of making it!&quot; <br>
Oh! Well put that way, and by her beloved mentor no less, what choice did she have? Besides this, she thought that to be able to make such a weapon would make her the happiest ranger alive! So she found her way to the fletching merchant in the Eastern Commonlands, after finally figuring out how to stuff her ears deaf to the raucous calls of people buying and selling their wares, why there were well over a hundred of them! She decided it would probably be a good idea to just grab twenty bundles of the cheapest version of each component and head to the Freeport bank to dust off her fletching kit and get started. <br>
<br>
<br>
So began the long trials and platinum burning tribulations of Tymoria's new trade. She spent most of her time either clearing the wretched orcs from the Orc Highway in Oasis or in that same merchants hut feverishly making arrow upon arrow upon arrow. Eventually; many, many seasons later; after a particularly nasty day in the Lake of Ill Omen, (her new hunting ground) She gave up on fighting entirely and committed herself to fletching. She had already achieved Master status, but she craved the title of Grandmaster like none other. <br>
<br>
<br>
Then there came a time that her guildmates began to despair that Tymoria would do anything but fletch and sell bows and arrows. All her hunting partners had already surpassed her in experience and it seemed she would never leave the merchant's life behind her and live the life of a ranger born. Finally one hot sunny day in the Eastern Commonlands, her fellow Arrow the dark elven mage Jojen passed by and began to converse with her. He had hunted with her merely once or twice, but they had had tremendous fun during those hunts and he missed her. He tried to figure out why she chose to shun adventure for fletching, clearly baffled by the whole situation. <br>
<br>
<br>
So it was that Tymoria confided in him her longing to attain the title of Grandmaster Fletcher. Nothing thrilled her more than to see a finished bow almost appear in her hands as if by magic and know that her hands were the ones that had crafted it. She had been given so much by the Arrows that she wanted to have a skill she could contribute to her small guild with. For at her experience of a mere twenty some odd seasons, she could not truly pay back the favors for quite some time to come. She simply was not capable of killing worthy enough foes to attain riches enough, nor could she afford to simply buy them trinkets or pay the favors in cash. He was surprised to say the least. He reminded her that nobody expected her to pay them back when bestowing these items upon her. She replied that yes, this is true, but she felt honor bound to do so none the less. <br>
<br>
<br>
At that point their conversation drifted to her craft and the cost of gaining skill in this trade. Tymoria, thinking that Jojen had at last been satisfied with her answers, answered everything Jojen asked as well as she knew how. He finally asked casually how much coin she thought it would take before she could attain the title of Grandmaster. She thought for a bit, and slowly replied that it would probably cost close to one thousand pieces of platinum, give or take a couple hundred pieces. Hearing this, Jojen stood and asked her to wait for a few minutes while he checked his bank. He thought he might have something that would aid her in her endeavor. Finally he returns saying that she would not be able to use the item he had planned on giving her, but that he had another thing that would probably help even more! Eagerly she asked him what that could be. No sooner had the words left her mouth then Jojen took her hand and closed it around a pouch that crackled like paper. She pulled it open curiously and gasped in shock at what she found there. A bank note redeemable for one thousand pieces of platinum! <br>
&quot;Great Karana!&quot; She thought, &quot;this is far too much!&quot; <br>
She then said as much to the grinning Dark elf, he simply said,<br>
&quot; All I ask is that you use this to achieve grandmaster status and then go out to experience life! I would love to go hunting with you again, but the game I hunt now is far to dangerous for you until you become more experienced. promise me this, and the money is yours gladly!&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
She stood in shock while he calmly walked on to his original destination and arranged for the first teleportation to North Karana she could find. She had to get to Surefall Glade so she could put this money to its best use possible; she always got wonderful treatment from the merchants there. <br>
